  "tcmTraditionalUsage": {
    "en": "This herb comes from the fruits of the Japanese Cornel Dogwood tree. Sour and warm in nature, it enters the kidney and liver meridians. Its uses include tonifying the liver and kidneys and retaining jing (kidney essence) and body fluids. It can treat conditions including excessive sweating, urinary incontinence, and problems arising from jing deficiency such as dizziness, vertigo and back pain.\n",
    "zh-Hant": "山茱萸味道酸澀，藥性微溫，歸肝、腎經，能補益肝腎，收斂固澀，用於治療肝腎虧虛導致的頭暈目眩、潮熱冒汗、腰膝酸軟、性功能下降、小便不利等，亦用於消渴病。\n",
    "zh-Hans": "山茱萸味道酸涩，药性微溫，歸肝、肾经，能补益肝肾，收斂固涩，用于治疗肝肾虧虚導致的头暈目眩、潮热冒汗、腰膝酸软、性功能下降、小便不利等，亦用于消渴病。\n"
  },
